Citation.sTitle: Experimental and predicted excess molar enthalpies of some working pairs for absorption cycles
Citation.sAbstract: In this work, the measured excess molar enthalpies of absorption heat pump working pairs (refrigerant  + absorbent), viz. water + mono-, di- and tri-ethylene glycol, water + glycerol, and ethanol + di- and  tri-ethylene glycol mixtures are presented at 298.15K and ambient pressure using a Setaram Calvet C80  calorimeter. The experimental results are represented and correlated by a Redlich Kister type equation.  Modeling of the excess enthalpies has been performed using the UNIFAC molecular group-contribution  method, and UNIQUAC Gibbs energy model. In addition, the data and results are used to predict the Gibbs  energy of all binary systems. This allows a preliminary evaluation of the suitability of the binary systems  as heat pump working pairs.
